The invention is now to be explained in detail by means of a preferred example and the accompanying figures, wherein:


FIG. 1 is a basic view, partially in section, of the invention from the side, in an upper position of the steering column, where only the essential elements are represented;


FIG. 2 is a view of the invention according to FIG. 1, but in a position of the steering column moved downward;


FIG. 3 is a view of the invention according to FIG. 2, but with the steering column moved out in the direction of the steering wheel;


FIG. 4 is a detail view of the casing part and the structural part serving to cover the gap in the brought-together state, in longitudinal section;


FIG. 5 is a basic representation of the invention of FIG. 3 from below;


FIG. 6 is a perspective basic representation of the invention, where the steering wheel is not shown;


FIG. 7 is a cross section along section VII in FIG. 4, without steering column and locking means.
